  sodium: 450 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Finely chop 2 tsp @thyme{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Trim, then halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, 1 tsp chopped thyme, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until lightly browned, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, poke @sweet potatoes{2} on all sides with a #fork{}. Place in a large #microwave-safe bowl{} and microwave until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Let cool slightly. Once Brussels sprouts have roasted 10 minutes, add sweet potatoes to baking sheet. Return to oven until veggies are tender, about ~{10%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @fall spice blend{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a medium pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in same pan used to cook pork chops over medium-high heat. Add shallot, remaining chopped thyme, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, about ~{1%minute}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water to pan. Reduce heat to medium low. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and any pork resting juices. Turn off heat.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a small #bowl{}. Microwave until softened, about ~{10%seconds}. Stir in @honey{1/2%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cut sweet potatoes lengthwise; fluff insides with a fork. Divide pork, sweet potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Top sweet potatoes with honey butter. Top pork with sauce.

> Best of fall flavors, delivered!